.TH man_1_simple_shell(3) "04 August 2022" "simple_shell_manual"

.B run with groff -man -Tascii man_1_simple_shell

.TH man_1_simple_shell(3)

.SH NAME
.B simple_shell: hsh
- a simplified UNIX command interpreter (shell)

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B This simple shell is executed by typing ./hsh

.B int main(void)

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
This shell is an end of trimester school project. Tries to imitate the function of a real shell.

.RS
.nf
- Works in interactive an non interactive mode
- Handles command with or without a full path
- Handles command with or without arguments
.RE


.SH BUILT-INS
.IP "env"
Prints the current enviroment

.IP "exit"
Exits the shell

.SH FILES
.TP
.I
/simple_shell/man_1_simple_shell

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.BI $ >/bin/ls
.TP
.PP
Runs the ls command in interactive mode.
.TP
.BI $>ls
.TP
.PP
Runs the ls command in interactive mode.

.TP
.BI $echo ls | ./hsh
.TP
.PP
Runs the command in non interactive mode.

.SH FOR INFO ON REAL SHELL SEE
.BR sh man page

